The GP said it ‘isn’t essential but would help, your assessment request may be denied without it’ - arguably being able to write one is a positive that you’re less affected by ADHD than some others who may struggle to even write the letter?? fucking do better guys, honestly.

They then asked me to write a letter describing how ADHD affects me, to send to the assessor to REQUEST to be assessed.
This is the exact kind of thing that can be very difficult for people with ADHD (concentration, organisation)

i can’t believe it, it took me months to even be able to land the initial appointment with my GP because of the absurd ‘call at 8:30 on the dot and maybe get an appointment’ system which is very ADHD un-friendly to begin with
